    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 550ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[775ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>vegetable stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> creamy vegetable stock </strong>and <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and cook for 15-18 min or until the potatoes are almost fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes<strong> </strong>are almost fork-tender, add your <strong>diced pollock</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> to the pot and cook for 4-5 min or until the pollock is cooked through and the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized <strong>diced pollock</strong>? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p><p>Season to taste with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pollock and potatoes are cooking, chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once everything is done, add the <strong>grated cheese</strong> to the pot and gently stir everything together \u2013 this is your<strong> one pot cheesy pollock & leek chowder</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-cheesy-pollock-and-leek-chowder/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot cheesy pollock & leek chowder</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped chives</strong> and season with a good grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
